📂 Project Structure

AI-Mail-Assistant/
│── backend/        # Spring Boot backend (API + Gemini Integration)
│── frontend/       # React frontend (UI for testing replies)
│── extension/      # Chrome extension (Gmail integration)
│── README.md       # Project documentation
│── .gitignore      # Ignore unnecessary files
│── package.json    # Frontend dependencies
│── pom.xml         # Backend dependencies

🚀 Getting Started

1️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/AI-Mail-Assistant.git
cd AI-Mail-Assistant

2️⃣ Setup & Run Backend (Spring Boot)

cd backend
mvn clean install
mvn spring-boot:run

3️⃣ Setup & Run Frontend (React)

cd frontend
npm install
npm start

4️⃣ Load Chrome Extension

Open Google Chrome → Go to chrome://extensions/

Enable Developer Mode (top right)

Click Load Unpacked → Select the extension/ folder

🎯 Usage

Open Gmail and click the AI Reply button in the toolbar.

The extension will fetch email content and generate a smart reply using Google Gemini AI.

You can insert the reply into your email with a single click.

🤖 Future Enhancements

🔹 Support for multiple AI models (e.g., GPT, Bard).

🔹 Customizable AI response styles.

🔹 Cloud deployment for real-time AI processing.

